This repository contains reproducible analysis scripts used for RNA-seq
processing and downstream differential abundance analysis using nf-core
pipelines and Singularity. It also includes R scripts for transcription
factor motif disruption analysis using motifbreakR (GRCh38, dbSNP155).

All scripts are structured for HPC execution and are anonymised for portability.
## Repository Structure

├── rnaseq/
│   ├── run_nfcore_rnaseq_WT_vs_rs77692262.sh
│   ├── run_nfcore_rnaseq_WT_vs_rs79724577_Primary.sh
│   ├── run_nfcore_rnaseq_rs77692262_Primary_vs_rs77692262_in_rs79724577_background.sh
│   ├── run_nfcore_rnaseq_rs77692262_vs_rs77692262_in_rs79724577_background.sh
│   └── ...
│
├── differential_abundance/
│   ├── run_nfcore_differentialabundance_WT_vs_rs77692262.sh
│   ├── run_nfcore_differentialabundance_WT_vs_rs79724577_Primary.sh
│   └── ...
│
├── motif_analysis/
│   └── run_motifbreakr_from_rsid.R

## Requirements

- Nextflow (≥22)
- Singularity or Apptainer
- nf-core/rnaseq
- nf-core/differentialabundance
- R (≥4.2)
- Bioconductor packages:
  - motifbreakR
  - MotifDb
  - BSgenome
  - SNPlocs.Hsapiens.dbSNP155.GRCh38

## Running nf-core/rnaseq

Edit the paths in the script and execute:

```bash
bash rnaseq/run_nfcore_rnaseq_WT_vs_R.sh

bash differential_abundance/run_nfcore_differentialabundance_WT_vs_R.sh


---

## Data Availability

Input FASTQ files and count matrices are not included in this repository.
Paths in scripts are placeholders and should be modified for local environments.

## Genome Build

All analyses use GRCh38 with Ensembl v111 annotation.

